{"id":14881768,"mediaExerciseId":"7ccaebf4-ffa3-4cd7-b365-5f03852089d9","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612470,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":736,"solutions":[{"id":5980286,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine which international capital market relationships is expected to hold most closely.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/b11334cac522c3e284d608645e62e923/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/b11334cac522c3e284d608645e62e923/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let us first define each international capital market relationship.\n\\\n**Relative Purchasing Power Parity** is a condition that determines the *change in the exchange rate* at some point in time. It tells us that there is an inverse relationship between the inflation rate and the value of the currency.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/066fabd92393200e67f23c184af37ae8/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/066fabd92393200e67f23c184af37ae8/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Interest Rate Parity** is a condition that states that the difference of the interest rates between two countries is the *same* as the difference of the forward exchange rate and the spot exchange rate in percentage.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/aa3f8d432abdebc01faf2479a0505dbc/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/aa3f8d432abdebc01faf2479a0505dbc/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**Unbiased Forward Rates** is a condition stating the current forward rate predicts the future spot exchange rate *unbiasedly*. Hence, the forward rate is equal to the expected future spot rate.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/4aa950ec4588742d56d09a5f5cb890b6/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/4aa950ec4588742d56d09a5f5cb890b6/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**Uncovered Interest Parity** is a condition stating that the expected percentage change in the exchange rate is the *same* as the difference in interest rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/bf26d48b1584a0720ea1dc18c5a74f52/lateximg_large.png","width":1053},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/bf26d48b1584a0720ea1dc18c5a74f52/lateximg.png","width":528}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Lastly, the **international fisher effect** states the the real rates are *equal* across the countries.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":63,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/04f3da5f5bfb75c811ee9721a5b826b5/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/04f3da5f5bfb75c811ee9721a5b826b5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"The international capital market relationship that is expected to hold most closely is the **interest rate parity (IRP)** since it is one of the basic method of showing international capital market relationship. Moreover, we can see how covered interest arbitrage holds the relationship of interest rates, forward exchange rate and the spot exchange rate clearly.\n\\\nHence, we can easily discover any arbitrage opportunity that may happen in the market through interest rate parity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/6df325eb90127085baa92a7c48361129/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/6df325eb90127085baa92a7c48361129/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we have determined  which international capital market relationships is expected to hold most closely - the **interest rate parity (IRP)**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/e385009aed3d0fd40a9f5a4d5c7fddde/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":54,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/59d0172728ffe79cd01e841866828e94/e385009aed3d0fd40a9f5a4d5c7fddde/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ddb5fae8-57f8-433f-8f0f-eed5a89eec52","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":8}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881769,"exerciseName":"1","page":736,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1b92e52c-278f-454f-a88d-c9b6235a6a54","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-1-1b92e52c-278f-454f-a88d-c9b6235a6a54"},{"id":14881770,"exerciseName":"2","page":736,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"128c11ec-0c32-4a2c-9e12-e45ab05a0878","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-2-128c11ec-0c32-4a2c-9e12-e45ab05a0878"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881767,"exerciseName":"9","page":736,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"68bd1e6d-d8c5-471b-b37d-b7ce66140de4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-9-68bd1e6d-d8c5-471b-b37d-b7ce66140de4"},{"id":14881766,"exerciseName":"8","page":735,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fcb0e8a4-9595-4bc7-90a5-a5538f4dbf16","_webUrl":"https://qu